            <h2 class="section-title">About Me</h2>
        </div>
    
        <div class="about-content">
            <div class="about-text">
                <p>

I am a dedicated researcher and the Laboratory Manager I for the Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering at Florida International University (FIU). I hold a Ph.D. in Civil Engineering (Water Resource Engineering) and an M.S. in Environmental Engineering from FIU, in addition to an M.S. in Mechanical Engineering (Fluid Mechanics and CFD). My research is centered on solving complex challenges in water resources, environmental science, and biomedical engineering through advanced computational modeling and artificial intelligence. 
</p><p>
My experience spans computational fluid dynamics (CFD), machine learning, and hardware prototyping. In water resource engineering, I specialize in developing and validating 3D numerical models for storm sewer geyser eruptions using OpenFOAM and deploying AI and digital twin models for managing stormwater infrastructure. My work in biomedical engineering includes modeling magnetic drug targeting in blood vessels and analyzing biomagnetic fluid flow using CFD. I also apply deep learning algorithms (CNNs) for diverse applications, such as the segmentation of brain lesions in MRI images , real-time prediction of air-water volume fractions , and diagnosing fatigue foot from biomechanical data. Furthermore, I have designed and prototyped an autonomous robot for surface water trash collection, which is part of an EPA proposal where I serve as Co-Principal Investigator.
</p><p>
In addition to my research, I am actively involved in the academic community. As Lab Manager at FIU, I direct research and teaching laboratories , manage detailed equipment and chemical inventories , and am tasked with developing and enforcing comprehensive laboratory safety protocols compliant with OSHA and EPA standards. I also serve as a Co-Principal Investigator on projects for the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and the National Science Foundation (NSF). Academically, I am a Guest Editor for a special issue of Pharmaceutics (Present) and have served as a Guest Editor for the Journal of Healthcare Engineering.

                </p>
                
